Luciana’s dream is to be the first person on Mars, and this realistic habitat helps her learn what it would be like to live and work on the red planet! The habitat offers three-sided play, with more than 40 science, technology, and health accessories to set up and rearrange:

core.title: Luciana's Space Suit for 18-inch Dolls
core.global_title_tag: Luciana's Space Suit for 18-inch Dolls | American Girl
core.global_description_tag: Luciana is excited to wear this space suit for her first Space Camp challenge! Comes with space gloves and space boots.

images.alt: American Girl Luciana's Space Suit for 18-inch Dolls

attributes.PLAgoogleprodtype: Apparel > Outfit Sets > Doll > GOTY > Luciana
attributes.MarketingDescription:
Luciana is excited to wear this space suit for her first Space Camp challenge! Features:
  • A space suit complete with authentic patches
  • An astronaut helmet with a clear visor that flips up
  • An equipment pack with faux knobs and dials that she needs for her first mission, along with authentic ID patches
  • Soft space gloves and a special mirror for her wrist that allows her to read the instruments on her equipment pack

  • A fun booklet explaining how space suits work
attributes.PLAgoogleprodcat: Toys & Games > Toys > Dolls, Playsets & Toy Figures > Doll & Action Figure Accessories
attributes.GeneralDisclosure: Quantity limited to three per order.
attributes.Tab1ContentCSR:
• Editorial comment: Along with the rest of her Odyssey team at Space Camp, Luciana wears a space suit for her first team mission: an EVA (extra-vehicular activity) in which team members are suspended above the International Space Station (ISS) simulator to replace tiles on the outside of the ISS as part of a materials experiment. Although Luciana finds it challenging to replace the tiles with her hands in astronaut gloves, she finds a creative solution to get the work done quickly, earning her the role of team captain!
  • Suit: Faux space suit in white woven fabric. Back Velcro. Patch details. Functioning pocket on right leg. Left side includes an attached fabric piece that secures with a plastic clasp. This mimics a safety tether to keep astronauts from drifting away in space. One end is attached to the astronaut and the other to the space craft.
  • Helmet: Molded plastic helmet with flip up transparent plastic visor. Faux lights on both sides.
  • Equipment pack
  • Front pack of space suit. Molded plastic with faux knob and dials. In real life is called the Displays and Control Module (DCM). Astronauts can operate their Primary Life Support Subsystem by adjusting switches, controls, and gauges.
  • Back pack of space suit. Molded plastic. It is officially referred to as the Primary Life Support Subsystem (PLSS). It supplies oxygen and removes carbon dioxide that is exhaled during a spacewalk. It also powers a fan that moves oxygen through the suit and life support systems. There are tanks that hold water that flows through a cooling and ventilation garment to keep the astronaut comfortable. A caution and warning system lets spacewalkers know if something is wrong with the suit.

core.title: Luciana's Telescope Projector Set
core.global_title_tag: Luciana's Telescope Projector Set | American Girl
core.global_description_tag: This set includes a toy telescope that lights up and projects space scenes, a tripod, a soft blanket to sit on, and a pretend smartphone.

images.alt: American Girl Luciana's Telescope Projector Set

attributes.Tab1ContentCSR:
• Editorial comment: Luciana’s team goes star gazing in Space Camp’s shuttle park and uses a telescope to see Mars.
  • Telescope: Plastic – Battery-operated projector with light inside. Light projects onto a wall. Has an internal image wheel with five space images permanently attached inside. The wheel can be rotated manually to switch the image. You won’t see anything if you look through the eyepiece. There is no way to “look through” anything and customers should avoid looking directly into the projector light. Projects best approx. 46” away. Approx. 6-3/8” long. Features a focus ring to clear the image depending how far away you are from the wall. Auto-off function that turns off the light after 90 seconds. Requires 3 AAA batteries, not included. Tripod: Plastic – Folds flat. The legs are extendable to make it taller. Telescope snaps on and off the Tripod. Approx. 11-1/2” high in tallest position.

images.alt: American Girl Luciana's Space Suit for 18-inch Dolls

attributes.PLAgoogleprodtype: Apparel > Outfit Sets > Doll > GOTY > Luciana
attributes.MarketingDescription:
Luciana is excited to wear this space suit for her first Space Camp challenge! Features:
  • A space suit complete with authentic patches
  • An astronaut helmet with a clear visor that flips up
  • An equipment pack with faux knobs and dials that she needs for her first mission, along with authentic ID patches
  • Soft space gloves and a special mirror for her wrist that allows her to read the instruments on her equipment pack
  • Durable space boots
  • A fun booklet explaining how space suits work
attributes.PLAgoogleprodcat: Toys & Games > Toys > Dolls, Playsets & Toy Figures > Doll & Action Figure Accessories
attributes.GeneralDisclosure: Quantity limited to three per order.
attributes.Tab1ContentCSR:
• Editorial comment: Along with the rest of her Odyssey team at Space Camp, Luciana wears a space suit for her first team mission: an EVA (extra-vehicular activity) in which team members are suspended above the International Space Station (ISS) simulator to replace tiles on the outside of the ISS as part of a materials experiment. Although Luciana finds it challenging to replace the tiles with her hands in astronaut gloves, she finds a creative solution to get the work done quickly, earning her the role of team captain!
  • Suit: Faux space suit in white woven fabric. Back Velcro. Patch details. Functioning pocket on right leg. Left side includes an attached fabric piece that secures with a plastic clasp. This mimics a safety tether to keep astronauts from drifting away in space. One end is attached to the astronaut and the other to the space craft.
  • Helmet: Molded plastic helmet with flip up transparent plastic visor. Faux lights on both sides.
  • Equipment pack
  • Front pack of space suit. Molded plastic with faux knob and dials. In real life is called the Displays and Control Module (DCM). Astronauts can operate their Primary Life Support Subsystem by adjusting switches, controls, and gauges.
  • Back pack of space suit. Molded plastic. It is officially referred to as the Primary Life Support Subsystem (PLSS). It supplies oxygen and removes carbon dioxide that is exhaled during a spacewalk. It also powers a fan that moves oxygen through the suit and life support systems. There are tanks that hold water that flows through a cooling and ventilation garment to keep the astronaut comfortable. A caution and warning system lets spacewalkers know if something is wrong with the suit.
